cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Trade Vulnerabilities Toolkit: A configuration-driven pipeline for UN COMTRADE data normalization and trade vulnerability analysis"
type: software

authors:
  - family-names: "Caur"
    given-names: "Jales"
    affiliation: "University of Brasília"
  - family-names: "Kreuz"
    given-names: "Jônatas"
    affiliation: "University of Brasília"

abstract: >-
  A configuration-driven Python pipeline for normalizing UN COMTRADE bilateral
  trade CSV exports and computing auditable trade vulnerability metrics. The
  toolkit implements standard trade economics measures (Herfindahl-Hirschman
  Index, Balassa RCA, Grubel-Lloyd IIT, Shannon entropy, CAGR, CV) alongside
  supply chain vulnerability indicators (bilateral exposure, dyadic asymmetry,
  top-supplier shock simulation, chokepoint scoring). All parameters are
  specified via YAML configuration files, enabling reproducible analysis of
  any HS6 product basket without code modification. Developed to support
  research on AI infrastructure trade vulnerabilities, but general-purpose
  by design.

repository-code: "https://github.com/jalescaur/trade-vulnerabilities-toolkit"
